thor/Kyung-Ok Cho","target":"Author/Kyung-Ok Cho","line":82},{"title":"Author/ChoKyung-Ok","target":"Author/ChoKyung-Ok","line":83},{"title":"Author/Kyung-Ok Cho","target":"Author/Kyung-Ok Cho","line":84},{"title":"PDF","target":"biblib/ryu_hericium_2017/ryu_hericium_2017.pdf","line":86}],"metadata":{"id":"ryu_hericium_2017","type":"article-journal","title":"Hericium erinaceus Extract Reduces Anxiety and Depressive Behaviors by Promoting Hippocampal Neurogenesis in the Adult Mouse Brain.","issued":{"date-parts":[[2017]]},"DOI":"10.1089/jmf.2017.4006","container-title":"Journal of Medicinal Food","abstract":"Abstract Versatile biological activities of Hericium erinaceus (HE) have been reported in many brain diseases. However, roles of HE in major psychiatric disorders such as depression and anxiety remain to be investigated. Therefore, we evaluated whether HE could reduce anxiety and depressive behaviors in the adult mouse and its underlying mechanisms. Male C57BL/6 mice were administered HE (20 or 60mg/kg, p.o.) or saline once a day for 4 weeks. Open field and tail suspension tests were performed 30min after the last administration of HE, followed by forced swim test 2 days later. We found that chronic administration of HE showed anxiolytic and antidepressant-like effects. To elucidate possible mechanisms, proliferative activity of the hippocampal progenitor cells was assessed by immunohistochemistry of proliferating cell nuclear antigen (PCNA) and Ki67. Moreover, to evaluate neuronal survival in the dentate gyrus, 5-bromo-2′-deoxyuridine (BrdU) (120mg/kg, i.p.) was given at the first day of HE administra...","tags":["#literature_note"],"author":[{"family":"Ryu","given":"Sun Young","literal":""},{"family":"Ryu","given":"Sun","literal":""},{"family":"RyuSun","given":"","literal":""},{"family":"Kim","given":"Hyoun Geun","literal":""},{"family":"Kim","given":"Hyoun Geun","literal":""},{"family":"Geun","given":"KimHyoun","literal":""},{"family":"Kim","given":"Joo Youn","literal":""},{"family":"Kim","given":"Joo Youn","literal":""},{"family":"Youn","given":"KimJoo","literal":""},{"family":"Kim","given":"Joo Youn","literal":""},{"family":"Kim","given":"Seong Yun","literal":""},{"family":"Yun","given":"KimSeong","literal":""},{"family":"Kim","given":"Seong Yun","literal":""},{"family":"Cho","given":"Kyung-Ok","literal":""},{"family":"ChoKyung-Ok","given":"","literal":""},{"family":"Cho","given":"Kyung-Ok","literal":""}],"citation-key":"ryu_hericium_2017","year":"2017","dateCreated":"2026-03-31","reading-status":"to-read","aliases":["Hericium erinaceus Extract Reduces Anxiety and Depressive Behaviors by Promoting Hippocampal Neurogenesis in the Adult Mouse Brain."],"author-links":["[[Author/Sun Young Ryu]]","[[Author/Sun Ryu]]","[[Author/RyuSun]]","[[Author/Hyoun Geun Kim]]","[[Author/Hyoun Geun Kim]]","[[Author/KimHyoun Geun]]","[[Author/Joo Youn Kim]]","[[Author/Joo Youn Kim]]","[[Author/KimJoo Youn]]","[[Author/Joo Youn Kim]]","[[Author/Seong Yun Kim]]","[[Author/KimSeong Yun]]","[[Author/Seong Yun Kim]]","[[Author/Kyung-Ok Cho]]","[[Author/ChoKyung-Ok]]","[[Author/Kyung-Ok Cho]]"],"attachment":["[[biblib/ryu_hericium_2017/ryu_hericium_2017.pdf|PDF]]"],"related":[[]]},"task_lines":[],"tasks":{},"codeblock_ranges":[],"last_embed":{"hash":"direpo","at":1774951887740}},"smart_blocks:Research/@ryu_hericium_2017.md#---frontmatter---": {"path":null,"embeddings":{"TaylorAI/bge-micro-v2":{"vec":[-0.0100044,0.02072333,0.02660679,-0.03142556,-0.02662293,0.07844942,0.01927732,0.05735603,-0.01143072,-0.04264692,0.02429596,-0.06235638,0.05221364,0.04167679,0.0056936,-0.0165997,-0.0295056,0.04294568,-0.08679389,-0.00583508,-0.03254252,-0.0606636,0.0296277,-0.02959207,0.00495977,0.01183885,-0.03508272,0.01115955,-0.03308443,-0.18487327,0.02360268,-0.02880365,0.05019184,-0.02638916,-0.00260579,0.01575146,-0.05471892,0.0272211,-0.04785177,0.05813838,0.06124938,0.03203683,0.01224965,0.01480955,0.05115005,-0.05363073,0.00873758,-0.12305842,0.0595284,